com.interpss.dstab.devent

Interface DynamicEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicEventImpl

    public interface DynamicEvent
extends NameTag
    A representation of the model object 'Dynamic Event'. It uses the status attribute to track its event. It is initialized as false. When t >= startTime and status = false, apply the evnet and set the status = true. Then when t >= startTime+duration, clear the event and set status = false. At any time, we cannot have more than one active events.

    The following features are supported:

    • Start Time Sec
    • Duration Sec
    • Type
    • Permanent
    • Branch Fault
    • Branch Dynamic Event
    • Bus Fault
    • Bus Dynamic Event
    See Also:
    DstabDeventPackage.getDynamicEvent()
